SIMPLE: intake
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intake
<hw>In"take`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The place
where water, air, or other substance is taken into a pipe, conduit, or
machine; -- opposed to <contr>outlet</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the beginning of a contraction or narrowing in a
tube or cylinder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The quantity taken in; <as>as, the <ex>intake</ex>
of air</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intaminated</ent>⟦br⟧
